{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17585966","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17585966"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T08:23:07+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T08:23:07+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15042"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15042","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15042"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.92,0.08,0,0,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7730"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67234"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7730","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7730"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15042"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52686"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4933"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"5090"},{"type":"tags","id":"7875"},{"type":"tags","id":"8115"},{"type":"tags","id":"8543"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"18880"},{"type":"contributions","id":"18883"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67234","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/67234"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EMultiple myeloma is a plasma cell malignancy with various systemic manifestations.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ELaboratory results typically show:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003ESerum calcium: elevated\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EHaemoglobin: decreased\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003ECreatinine: elevated\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EAlbumin: decreased\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes a characteristic feature of multiple myeloma?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Hypercalcaemia, renal failure, anaemia and bone lesions are typical features","Free light chains directly damage tubular cells through cytotoxicity","Serum albumin levels are consistently elevated","Plasma cell numbers remain within normal limits","Light chain proteins cannot form tubular casts"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EMultiple myeloma is characterized by the CRAB criteria:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHypercalcaemia, renal failure, anaemia and bone lesions\u003C/strong\u003E form the classic tetrad of findings that define the condition\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFree light chains directly damage tubular cells through cytotoxicity\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect - they cause renal damage primarily through cast formation with Tamm-Horsfall protein in distal tubules\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESerum albumin levels are consistently elevated\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect - albumin is typically decreased due to reduced production\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPlasma cell numbers remain within normal limits\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect - plasma cells are markedly increased due to malignant proliferation\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELight chain proteins cannot form tubular casts\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect - they readily combine with Tamm-Horsfall protein to form obstructive casts\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe combination of these features, along with evidence of clonal plasma cell proliferation in the bone marrow, helps establish the diagnosis of multiple myeloma.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Multiple myeloma features hypercalcaemia, renal failure, anaemia and bone lesions (CRAB criteria)","Bence Jones proteins are free light chains that damage renal tubules through cast formation with Tamm-Horsfall protein","Multiple myeloma is characterized by abnormal plasma cell proliferation and decreased albumin production"],"references":["Cowan AJ, Green DJ, Kwok M, Lee S, Coffey DG, Holmberg LA, Tuazon S, Gopal AK, Libby EN. Diagnosis and Management of Multiple Myeloma: A Review. JAMA. 2022 Feb 1;327(5):464-477. doi: 10.1001/jama.2022.0003. PMID: 35103762.","Jennette, J. C., \u0026 D\u0027Agati, V. D. (2023). Heptinstall\u0027s Pathology of the Kidney. Lippincott Williams \u0026 Wilkins","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52686"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15042"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52686","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/52686"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-04T09:18:49+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-01T18:48:25+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7730"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67234"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tag